ecological study, LEFAM would better explain the year to year changes of the 
resources in the health sector, measured in terms of the human resources (R = 
0.96), the hospital beds per thousand persons (R = -0.86), and would also 
increase the relation with other health indicators such as infant mortality rate 
(R = 0.98) and mortality rate (R = 0.59) as compared with life expectancy alone.

